!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

incarnate TEM8

1. ADJ If you say that someone is a quality incarnate , you mean that they represent that quality or are typical of it in an extreme form. 化身的; 极典型的 [n ADJ] 

例： She is evil incarnate. 她是邪恶的化身。 

2. ADJ You use incarnate to say that something, especially a god or spirit, is represented in human form. (神或灵)人格化; 显形的 [v-link ADJ] 

例： Why should God become incarnate as a male? 为什么上帝显身为男性呢？ 

3. V-T If you say that a quality is incarnated in a person, you mean that they represent that quality or are typical of it in an extreme form. 表现; 最典型体现 

例： The iniquities of the regime are incarnated in one man. 该体制的种种劣迹集中体现于一人。 

例： ...a writer who incarnates the changing consciousness of the Americas. ...典型地体现出美洲观念变化的一位作家。 

4. V-T If you say that someone or something is incarnated in a particular form, you mean that they appear on earth in that form. 化身为; 显形为 [usu passive] 

例： The god Vishnu was incarnated on earth as a king. 毗瑟挐神在地上化身为一位国王。

